snippet: A compilation of Jenni Rivera’s music was released just days after the singer’s death; the saxophonist Jason Robinson examines jazz dualities in “Tiresian Symmetry.”
abstract: Jon Pareles reviews compilation album La Misma Gran Senora by Mexican-American singer Jenni Rivera; Nate Chinen reviews Tiresian Symmetry, newest release by jazz saxophonist Jason Robinson.

byline.original: By JON PARELES and NATE CHINEN

lead_paragraph: A compilation of Jenni Rivera’s music was released just days after the singer’s death; the saxophonist Jason Robinson examines jazz dualities in “Tiresian Symmetry.”

headline.seo: ‘La Misma Gran Senora’ by Jenni Rivera and ‘Tiresian Symmetry’ by Jason Robinson
